# Interactive Used Vehicle Market Dashboard

## Overview
This repository contains an interactive web application that allows users to explore used vehicle market data through dynamic visualisations.

The application is built with **Python and Streamlit** and provides a simple interface to analyse vehicle attributes such as mileage and pricing. It is designed for quick exploratory analysis by non-technical users and stakeholders.

---

## Application Features
- Interactive histogram for exploring vehicle attributes
- Scatter plot to analyse relationships between variables
- User controls (buttons or checkboxes) to toggle visualisations
- Responsive layout suitable for browser-based access

---

## Live Demo
The application is deployed and accessible via the following URL:

https://<APP_NAME>.onrender.com/


> Note: The application may take a few seconds to load if it has been inactive.

---

## How to Run the Application Locally

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<YOUR_USERNAME>/used-vehicle-market-dashboard.git
cd used-vehicle-market-dashboard

### 2. Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv vehicles_env
source vehicles_env/bin/activate  # macOS / Linux
vehicles_env\Scripts\activate     # Windows

### 3. Install dependencies
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

### 4. Run the application
streamlit run app.py
The app will be available in your browser at:
http://localhost:8501

Deployment
The application is deployed as a cloud-based service using Render.
Any updates pushed to the main branch can be redeployed manually via the Render dashboard.



